[{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"CurrentModule = BallroomSkatingSystem","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#API","page":"API Reference","title":"API","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"Modules = [BallroomSkatingSystem]","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#BallroomSkatingSystem.calc_majority-Tuple{Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"BallroomSkatingSystem.calc_majority","text":"calc_majority(results)\n\nReturns the judge majority for a result DataFrame results.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#BallroomSkatingSystem.get_places-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"BallroomSkatingSystem.get_places","text":"get_places(dances, results_single_dances)\n\nCollects the skating results for a vector of dances and result DataFrames.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#BallroomSkatingSystem.get_rule11_table-Tuple{Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"BallroomSkatingSystem.get_rule11_table","text":"get_rule11_table(results_single_dances)\n\nPrepares a DataFrame with all judgements concatenated into a single table for use when  applying Rule 11.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#BallroomSkatingSystem.prepare_sums-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"BallroomSkatingSystem.prepare_sums","text":"prepare_sums(results, depth)\n\nReturns the DataFrame for the calculation of the majority of votes, as well as the sum of evaluations up to a given rank.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#BallroomSkatingSystem.remove!-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"BallroomSkatingSystem.remove!","text":"remove!(a, item)\n\nRemoves item from the collection a.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#BallroomSkatingSystem.skating_combined-NTuple{4, Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"BallroomSkatingSystem.skating_combined","text":"skating_combined(dances, results_single_dances)\n\nCalculates the final placement of competitors in a dancing competition based on the skating rules. dances is a vector of strings, containing the names of the dances.  results_single_dances is a vector of DataFrames, containing the results for the individual dances. See skating_single_dance for the correct input format.\n\nOutputs a DataFrame with the accumulated skating tableau as strings, a vector containing  tableaus containing the application of Rule 10 and Rule 11, the skating results for the individual dances as well as a DataFrame with the starter numbers and final places.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#BallroomSkatingSystem.skating_single_dance-Tuple{DataFrame, Int64}","page":"API Reference","title":"BallroomSkatingSystem.skating_single_dance","text":"skating_single_dance(results)\nskating_single_dance(results, majority_from; [initial_place, initial_column, depth])\n\nCalculates a skating tableau and placement for judgment results of a single dance contained in the DataFrame results. It must contain the starter numbers of the dancers as a first column named :Numbers, and the places assigned by the different judges in the following columns, for example as in\n\nDataFrame(Number = [11, 12, 13, 14, 15],\n        JudgeA = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5],\n        JudgeB = [1, 3, 2, 4, 5],\n        JudgeC = [1, 3, 2, 5, 4],\n        JudgeD = [5, 1, 2, 3, 4],\n        JudgeE = [2, 1, 5, 3, 4])\n\nReturns a DataFrame with the skating tableau represented as strings, as well as a DataFrame with the starter numbers and places.\n\nFor calculations on cropped tables, the majority of votes, the initial placement to fill, the initial column in the tableau where skating should start as well as the desired depth of the calculation can be defined by keyword arguments.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#BallroomSkatingSystem.write_places!-NTuple{6, Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"BallroomSkatingSystem.write_places!","text":"write_places!(places, places_text, index, current_place)\nwrite_places!(places, places_text, index, place_to_write, current_place)    \nwrite_places!(places, places_text, index, place_to_write, place_to_write_text, current_place)\n\nWrite the result of the skating procedure to the DataFrames containing the final calculation.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#BallroomSkatingSystem.write_result!-NTuple{8, Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"BallroomSkatingSystem.write_result!","text":"write_result!(calculation, calculation_text, sum_of_eval, id, current_place, current_col, tmp_col, max_cols; append_sum = false)\n\nWrite the result of the skating procedure to the DataFrames containing placement and summary information. Remove the parts that are not needed anymore.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"CurrentModule = BallroomSkatingSystem","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/#Examples","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/#Single-Dances","page":"Examples","title":"Single Dances","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"Following Wikipedia, we can obtain places for the following results after judging:","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/#Results-with-a-Clear-Majority-for-Each-Place","page":"Examples","title":"Results with a Clear Majority for Each Place","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"With judges as A,...,E and competitors 11, 12 and 13, we have the following places:","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"Competitor A B C D E\n11 1 1 2 1 2\n12 2 2 1 3 1\n13 3 3 3 2 3","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"We create a DataFrame with these results","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"using BallroomSkatingSystem # hide\nresults = DataFrame(Number = [11, 12, 13],\n        JudgeA = [1, 2, 3],\n        JudgeB = [1, 2, 3],\n        JudgeC = [2, 1, 3],\n        JudgeD = [1, 3, 2],\n        JudgeE = [2, 1, 3])\nnothing # hide","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"and obtain the final results by","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"calculation, places = skating_single_dance(results)\nnothing # hide","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"The output contains the full calculation as a dataframe","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"calculation","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"as well as just the places:","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"places","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/#No-Majority","page":"Examples","title":"No Majority","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"With the following judgements ","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"Competitor A B C D E\n11 1 1 2 2 3\n12 2 2 1 1 2\n13 3 3 3 3 1","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"we obtain","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"results = DataFrame(Number = [11, 12, 13],\n        JudgeA = [1, 2, 3],\n        JudgeB = [1, 2, 3],\n        JudgeC = [2, 1, 3],\n        JudgeD = [2, 1, 3],\n        JudgeE = [3, 2, 1])\ncalculation, places = skating_single_dance(results)\ncalculation","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/#Shared-Places-and-Wins-with-2nd-Place","page":"Examples","title":"Shared Places and Wins with 2nd Place","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"Competitor A B C D E\n11 1 1 3 3 4\n12 2 2 2 2 2\n13 3 3 4 1 1\n14 4 4 1 4 3","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"gives","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"results = DataFrame(Number = [11, 12, 13, 14],\n        JudgeA = [1, 2, 3, 4],\n        JudgeB = [1, 2, 3, 4],\n        JudgeC = [3, 2, 4, 1],\n        JudgeD = [3, 2, 1, 4],\n        JudgeE = [4, 2, 1, 3])\ncalculation, places = skating_single_dance(results)\ncalculation","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/#Multiple-Dances","page":"Examples","title":"Multiple Dances","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/#st-Example","page":"Examples","title":"1st Example","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"The following examples are from the TSO Homepage (in German).","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"Assume we have a tournament with the following dances","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"Waltz (abbreviated W)\nTango (T)\nViennese Waltz (V)\nSlowfox (S)\nQuickstep (Q)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"and the following individual placements from the judges:","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"Nr. W-A W-B W-C W-D W-E T-A T-B T-C T-D T-E V-A V-B V-C V-D V-E S-A S-B S-C S-D S-E Q-A Q-B Q-C Q-D Q-E\n25 1 1 2 5 3 1 2 2 3 4 1 1 2 2 3 2 2 5 1 5 2 6 2 6 1\n35 2 2 5 2 5 5 3 1 2 2 3 2 1 1 2 1 1 2 5 2 1 5 1 5 2\n45 4 5 3 1 1 3 1 3 1 3 5 3 3 6 1 5 6 3 2 3 3 2 4 2 4\n55 3 3 6 3 6 4 4 4 4 1 2 6 6 3 4 3 3 1 3 6 5 1 5 1 3\n65 6 6 1 4 4 2 5 5 5 5 4 4 5 5 6 6 4 6 6 4 4 4 6 3 6\n75 5 4 4 6 2 6 6 6 6 6 6 5 4 4 5 4 5 4 4 1 6 3 3 4 5","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"We set up the results as follows:","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"using BallroomSkatingSystem # hide\ndances = [\"Waltz\", \"Tango\", \"Viennese Waltz\", \"Slowfox\", \"Quickstep\"]\n\nresultsW = DataFrame(Number = [25, 35, 45, 55, 65, 75],\n    JudgeA = [1, 2, 4, 3, 6, 5],\n    JudgeB = [1, 2, 5, 3, 6, 4],\n    JudgeC = [2, 5, 3, 6, 1, 4],\n    JudgeD = [5, 2, 1, 3, 4, 6],\n    JudgeE = [3, 5, 1, 6, 4, 2])\n\nresultsT = DataFrame(Number = [25, 35, 45, 55, 65, 75],\n    JudgeA = [1, 5, 3, 4, 2, 6],\n    JudgeB = [2, 3, 1, 4, 5, 6],\n    JudgeC = [2, 1, 3, 4, 5, 6],\n    JudgeD = [3, 2, 1, 4, 5, 6],\n    JudgeE = [4, 2, 3, 1, 5, 6])\n\nresultsV = DataFrame(Number = [25, 35, 45, 55, 65, 75],\n    JudgeA = [1, 3, 5, 2, 4, 6],\n    JudgeB = [1, 2, 3, 6, 4, 5],\n    JudgeC = [2, 1, 3, 6, 5, 4],\n    JudgeD = [2, 1, 6, 3, 5, 4],\n    JudgeE = [3, 2, 1, 4, 6, 5])\n\nresultsS = DataFrame(Number = [25, 35, 45, 55, 65, 75],\n    JudgeA = [2, 1, 5, 3, 6, 4],\n    JudgeB = [2, 1, 6, 3, 4, 5],\n    JudgeC = [5, 2, 3, 1, 6, 4],\n    JudgeD = [1, 5, 2, 3, 6, 4],\n    JudgeE = [5, 2, 3, 6, 4, 1])\n\nresultsQ = DataFrame(Number = [25, 35, 45, 55, 65, 75],\n    JudgeA = [2, 1, 3, 5, 4, 6],\n    JudgeB = [6, 5, 2, 1, 4, 3],\n    JudgeC = [2, 1, 4, 5, 6, 3],\n    JudgeD = [6, 5, 2, 1, 3, 4],\n    JudgeE = [1, 2, 4, 3, 6, 5])\n\nresults = [resultsW, resultsT, resultsV, resultsS, resultsQ]\nnothing # hide","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"We calculate the final result by","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"places_text, rule10_11, reports, places = skating_combined(dances, results)\nnothing # hide","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"We can see the final placement in the places DataFrame:","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"places","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"The calculation of the sum of the individual places can be found in the first return value","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"places_text","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"In this example, Rule 11 needed to be applied. The separate calculations are reported for Rule 10 in","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"rule10_11[1]","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"and for Rule 11 in ","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"rule10_11[2]","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"Finally, reports contains the calculations for the individual dances (similar to the first section).","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/#nd-Example","page":"Examples","title":"2nd Example","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"Consider the following results","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"Nr. W-A W-B W-C W-D W-E T-A T-B T-C T-D T-E V-A V-B V-C V-D V-E S-A S-B S-C S-D S-E Q-A Q-B Q-C Q-D Q-E\n27 2 2 5 2 5 1 2 2 3 4 1 1 1 1 1 3 3 1 3 6 2 6 2 6 1\n37 3 3 6 3 6 3 1 3 1 3 2 3 4 5 6 1 1 2 5 2 4 4 6 3 6\n47 4 5 3 1 1 2 5 5 5 5 3 4 5 6 2 4 5 4 4 1 1 5 1 5 2\n57 1 1 2 5 3 4 4 4 4 1 4 5 6 2 3 5 6 3 2 3 6 3 3 4 5\n67 6 6 1 4 4 6 6 6 6 6 5 2 2 3 4 2 2 5 1 5 5 1 5 1 4\n77 5 4 4 6 2 5 3 1 2 2 6 6 3 4 5 6 4 6 6 4 3 2 4 2 3","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"We set up and run the calculations:","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"dances = [\"Waltz\", \"Tango\", \"Viennese Waltz\", \"Slowfox\", \"Quickstep\"]\n\nresultsW = DataFrame(Number = [27, 37, 47, 57, 67, 77],\n        JudgeA = [2, 3, 4, 1, 6, 5],\n        JudgeB = [2, 3, 5, 1, 6, 4],\n        JudgeC = [5, 6, 3, 2, 1, 4],\n        JudgeD = [2, 3, 1, 5, 4, 6],\n        JudgeE = [5, 6, 1, 3, 4, 2])\n\n    resultsT = DataFrame(Number = [27, 37, 47, 57, 67, 77],\n        JudgeA = [1, 3, 2, 4, 6, 5],\n        JudgeB = [2, 1, 5, 4, 6, 3],\n        JudgeC = [2, 3, 5, 4, 6, 1],\n        JudgeD = [3, 1, 5, 4, 6, 2],\n        JudgeE = [4, 3, 5, 1, 6, 2])\n\n    resultsV = DataFrame(Number = [27, 37, 47, 57, 67, 77],\n        JudgeA = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6],\n        JudgeB = [1, 3, 4, 5, 2, 6],\n        JudgeC = [1, 4, 5, 6, 2, 3],\n        JudgeD = [1, 5, 6, 2, 3, 4],\n        JudgeE = [1, 6, 2, 3, 4, 5])\n\n    resultsS = DataFrame(Number = [27, 37, 47, 57, 67, 77],\n        JudgeA = [3, 1, 4, 5, 2, 6],\n        JudgeB = [3, 1, 5, 6, 2, 4],\n        JudgeC = [1, 2, 4, 3, 5, 6],\n        JudgeD = [3, 5, 4, 2, 1, 6],\n        JudgeE = [6, 2, 1, 3, 5, 4])\n\n    resultsQ = DataFrame(Number = [27, 37, 47, 57, 67, 77],\n        JudgeA = [2, 4, 1, 6, 5, 3],\n        JudgeB = [6, 4, 5, 3, 1, 2],\n        JudgeC = [2, 6, 1, 3, 5, 4],\n        JudgeD = [6, 3, 5, 4, 1, 2],\n        JudgeE = [1, 6, 2, 5, 4, 3])\n\nresults = [resultsW, resultsT, resultsV, resultsS, resultsQ]\nplaces_text, rule10_11, reports, places = skating_combined(dances, results)\nnothing # hide","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"We obtain the following final places","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"places_text","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"Calculations for Rule 10:","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"rule10_11[1]","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"...and for Rule 11:","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"rule10_11[2]","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = BallroomSkatingSystem","category":"page"},{"location":"#BallroomSkatingSystem","page":"Home","title":"BallroomSkatingSystem","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for BallroomSkatingSystem.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"This package implements the skating system of compiling scores in ballroom dance competitions. ","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"warning: Disclaimer\nThis package has not been tested against all corner cases that might emerge in real dancing tournaments. ","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"note: Note\nNo sanity checks are performed on the data, like ensuring the correct number of judges for every dance, or making sure that starter numbers coincide. Make sure to feed sanitized data to the functions.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Installation","page":"Home","title":"Installation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"BallroomSkatingSystem.jl is a registered package. To install, type ] at the Julia REPL to enter package mode, and type","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"add BallroomSkatingSystem","category":"page"},{"location":"#Exported-Functions","page":"Home","title":"Exported Functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"skating_single_dance\nskating_combined ","category":"page"},{"location":"#BallroomSkatingSystem.skating_single_dance","page":"Home","title":"BallroomSkatingSystem.skating_single_dance","text":"skating_single_dance(results)\nskating_single_dance(results, majority_from; [initial_place, initial_column, depth])\n\nCalculates a skating tableau and placement for judgment results of a single dance contained in the DataFrame results. It must contain the starter numbers of the dancers as a first column named :Numbers, and the places assigned by the different judges in the following columns, for example as in\n\nDataFrame(Number = [11, 12, 13, 14, 15],\n        JudgeA = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5],\n        JudgeB = [1, 3, 2, 4, 5],\n        JudgeC = [1, 3, 2, 5, 4],\n        JudgeD = [5, 1, 2, 3, 4],\n        JudgeE = [2, 1, 5, 3, 4])\n\nReturns a DataFrame with the skating tableau represented as strings, as well as a DataFrame with the starter numbers and places.\n\nFor calculations on cropped tables, the majority of votes, the initial placement to fill, the initial column in the tableau where skating should start as well as the desired depth of the calculation can be defined by keyword arguments.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#BallroomSkatingSystem.skating_combined","page":"Home","title":"BallroomSkatingSystem.skating_combined","text":"skating_combined(dances, results_single_dances)\n\nCalculates the final placement of competitors in a dancing competition based on the skating rules. dances is a vector of strings, containing the names of the dances.  results_single_dances is a vector of DataFrames, containing the results for the individual dances. See skating_single_dance for the correct input format.\n\nOutputs a DataFrame with the accumulated skating tableau as strings, a vector containing  tableaus containing the application of Rule 10 and Rule 11, the skating results for the individual dances as well as a DataFrame with the starter numbers and final places.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#More-Information","page":"Home","title":"More Information","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Wiki page for the Skating system\nWDSF pdf file of the rules (see also this page)\nDescription of the rules (in German)","category":"page"}]
